title: East college football roundup: Princeton falls to Brown
text:
East college football roundup: Princeton falls to Brown October 18, 2015 Last updated: Sunday, October 18, 2015, 1:21 AM FROM NEWS SERVICE REPORTS | Print 
Johnny Pena scored on a 7-yard run with 57 seconds remaining and Brown beat Princeton, 38-31, Saturday in Providence, R.I. 
Pena's score came on a five-play, 42-yard drive after Princeton's Chad Kanoff was hit while trying to throw and his pass was intercepted by Will Twyman. 
Princeton (4-1, 1-1 Ivy) rallied from a 21-7 deficit to tie it twice, the final time at 31-all with 10 minutes left on Kanoff's 10-yard score to Scott Carpenter. 
Brown never trailed, taking the lead on the game's first play when Alexander Jette returned the kickoff 99 yards. 
The game matched Princeton's league-leading rushing offense against the Ivy's best passing offense of Brown (3-2, 1-1). The teams combined for 924 yards, though Princeton led with 373 yards passing and Brown with 192 rushing. 
Brown snapped Princeton's four-game winning streak and beat the Tigers for the first time in four games. 
PENN 42, COLUMBIA 7 (at New York) — Alek Torgersen threw three touchdown passes, Tre Solomon ran for two scores and the Quakers (2-3) beat the Lions (1-4) to give coach Ray Priore his first Ivy League win. 
Penn has beaten Columbia the last 19 times they have played, the longest active winning streak over an annual opponent in the FCS. 
VIRGINIA 44, SYRACUSE 38, 3OT (at Charlottesville, Va.) — Jordan Ellis scored on a 3-yard run in the third overtime and the Cavaliers (2-4) ended their two-game losing streak by rallying to beat the Orange (3-3), who lost their third straight. 
SOUTH FLORIDA 28, UCONN 20 (at East Hartford, Conn.) — .Quinton Flowers threw for 157 yards and two touchdowns and ran for 98 yards and another as the Bulls (3-3) beat the Huskies (3-4). 
ARMY 21, BUCKNELL 14 (at West Point, N.Y.) — A.J. Schurr came off the bench to run for two touchdowns and threw for the winning score to help the Black Knights (2-5) beat the Bison (3-3). 
FORDHAM 47, HOLY CROSS 41, OT (at New York) — Chase Edmonds (162 yards) ran for four touchdowns, including the game-winner, to lead the Rams (7-1) past the Crusaders (2-4). 
MONMOUTH 20, LIBERTY 17, OT (at West Long Branch) — Matt White kicked a 35-yard field goal on the final play of regulation then kicked a 37-yarder in overtime to lift the Hawks (3-4) past the Flames (3-4). 
MONTCLAIR ST. 33, CHRISTOPHER NEWPORT 22 (at Montclair) — Denzel Nieves ran for 104 yards and touchdowns and Ryan Davies (176 yards) threw for two scores to lead the Red Hawks (3-3). 
SALISBURY 62, WILLIAM PATERSON 33 (at Salisbury, Md.) — Dwaine Dabney ran for 176 yards and two touchdowns, but the Pioneers (1-5) lost to the Sea Gulls (4-1).
